column1: Supplemental Table 1. List of EI and LEIsc values for all 4096 hexamers from five locations.
In column 28, a label V denotes the splicing effect of this 6-mer has been experimentally validated.
In the column "Assignment", "E" represents ESEseq, "S" signifies ESSseq and "N" means neutral motifs.
In columns 31 to 36, a "+" means the sequence is found in the indicated motif list.
Input and output counts are the sums of duplicate experiments.

column2: Ke et al. 2008 Genome Research 18(4):533-43; Zhang et al. 2004 Genes & Development 18(11):1241-50. PESE hex are hexamers that occur six times or more in PESE octamers; PESS hex are defined similarly.
Smith et al. 2006 Human Molecular Genetics 15(16):2490-508
